article_title: Body of missing 72-year-old Virginia woman Emily Lu found; former tenant charged with murder
meta_description: A tenant who lived with 72-year-old Emily Lu has been arrested and and is charged with second-degree murder after her body was found this week, seven weeks after she disappeared from her home in Lorton, Virginia. She was last seen on security video at the Aldi in Gordon Plaza in Woodbridge, Virginia on June 3, 2021. A welfare check was conducted the next day when she didn’t show up to work. Brian George Sayrs Jr. was arrested and faces a charge of second-degree murder in the case. The Fairfax County Police Department is investigating.
